<DOC><DOCNO> AP881005-0279 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-05-88 1116EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Coleman-Chairman     10-05 0156</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Coleman-Chairman,0165</SECOND><HEAD>Grandson Of Coleman Co. Founder Elected Board Chairman</HEAD><DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sheldon C. Coleman, grandson of the ColemanCompany Inc.'s founder, has been elected company board chairman.   The younger Coleman succeeds his father, Sheldon Coleman, whodied Sept. 21 at age 86.   Coleman, the 88-year-old company's third chairman, also ispresident and chief executive officer. Founder W.C. Coleman waschairman until his death in 1957.   Coleman, 35, first worked for the company in factory productionjobs during high school and college. He served in various postsbefore becoming vice president and general manager of Coleman'slargest division, Group One, in 1984. He was named president lastyear. His election to the chairmanship was announced Tuesday.   Coleman has a bachelor's degree from the University of Kansasand a master's from California State University-Fullerton.   The Coleman Co., with approximately $265 million in assets,manufactures outdoor recreation equipment and home heating and airconditioning products.</TEXT></DOC>